result.execSummary:
The defendant Donald Ray Williams was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Intimidate Victim/Threaten Force, etc. [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Surcharge], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.45(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Original SENTENCING Transcript (19 pages) commencing 10/21/2015 received and filed.  CH

Defendant Donald Ray Williams in court with attorney Parker Charles Mathers.  Defendant Donald Ray Williams in custody.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by all parties to the court.  Additional statement by Theresa J.
AS to count 2:   The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 38 MONTHS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, credit for 169 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 23 MONTHS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 15 MONTHS with the following conditions:
-The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
-Pay all costs, assessments and victim/witness surcharges.
-Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
-Court will modify to NO VIOLENT CONTACT ORDER with Theresa J.
The defendant is advised as a convicted felon he may not carry or possess any firearms/body armor.
The court advises the defendant that voting privileges are suspended during the length of this sentence.
The defendant is given a written explanation of the determinate sentence, and is to be advised of his appeal rights by defense counsel.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.   
The defendant is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant remanded.
Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 21, 2015 at 08:15 am.

Defendant Donald Ray Williams in court with Attorney Parker Charles Mathers.  Defendant Donald Ray Williams in custody.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant has two cases before the court.

As to Count 2:
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court orders "use of a dangerous weapon" penalty enhancer dismissed.

Defendant waives constitutional rights, enters a plea of GUILTY to the amended charge and is examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the Complaint as a factual basis for judgment.  Court finds defendant guilty of the amended charge and enters a judgment of conviction.
COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms or body armor, he must provide a DNA sample and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

As to Count 1 and Count 3 and Count 4:
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court orders Counts 1, 3 and 4 DISMISSED but read-in as to sentencing.

Court orders case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 38.  No PSI ordered.  Court orders defendant remanded into the custody of the sheriff pending sentencing.

Jury trial is vacated.
